{"id":"2301.12273","submitter":"Jiongzhi Zheng","authors":"Jiongzhi Zheng, Changpeng Lin, Chongjia Lin, Ruiqiang Guo, Baoling\n  Huang","title":"Strong Anharmonic Phonon Renormalization and Dominant Role of Wave-like\n  Tunnelling of Phonons in Thermal Transport in Lead-free Halide Double\n  Perovskites","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mtrl-sci","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  We thoroughly investigate the microscopic mechanisms of anharmonic lattice\ndynamics and thermal transport in lead-free halide double perovskite Cs2AgBiBr6\nby coupling a first principles-based self-consistent phonon calculation with\nbubble diagram correction and a unified theory of lattice thermal transport\nconsidering both the particle-like phonon propagation and wave-like tunnelling\nof phonons. This methodology predicts an ultra-low thermal conductivity (e.g.,\n~0.21 Wm-1K-1 at 300 K) with extremely weak temperature dependence following\n~T-0.45, in sharp contrast to the conventionally predicted ~T-1 dependence.\nParticularly, we find that the vibrational properties of Cs2AgBiBr6 are\nfeatured by strong anharmonicity and wave-like tunnelling of phonons. On one\nhand, anharmonic phonon renormalization from both the cubic and quartic\nanharmonicities are essential in precisely predicting the experimentally\nmeasured phase transition temperature in Cs2AgBiBr6. On the other hand, the\nthermal conductivity contribution of the wavelike tunnelling channel surpasses\nthat of the particle-like propagation channel above around 340 K, indicating\nthe breakdown of the particle-like phonon picture conventionally used in the\nPeierls-Boltzmann Transport Equation (PBTE). Importantly, for thermal transport\nin Cs2AgBiBr6, considering only three-phonon or both three- and four-phonon\nscattering processes in phonon scattering rates will result in completely\ndifferent heat conductance mechanisms, revealing the importance of four-phonon\nprocesses. Our work highlights the importance of lattice anharmonicity and\nwave-like tunnelling of phonons in predicting ultra-low thermal conductivity of\nCs2AgBiBr6.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 28 Jan 2023 19:11:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Feb 2023 18:27:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-20"}
